---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "SAMI Survey: Internal Orbital Structure - ArXiv Atlas";
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>The SAMI Galaxy Survey: Internal Orbital Structure Across the Colour-Magnitude Diagram</h1>
      <div class="page-meta">
        <span class="tag">arXiv:2603.09917</span>
        <span class="tag">2026-03-11</span>
        <span class="tag">astro-ph.GA</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <h2 id="section-0">Overview</h2>
      <p>
        JAM dynamical modeling of 2,945 SAMI galaxies reveals orbital differences between red sequence and blue cloud galaxies.
      </p>

      <h2 id="section-1">Key Findings</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Red sequence galaxies</strong>: more radially biased orbits (β ≈ 0.3)</li>
        <li><strong>Blue cloud galaxies</strong>: more isotropic orbits (β ≈ 0.1)</li>
        <li><strong>Transition mass</strong>: M* ≈ 10^10.5 M☉ marks shift from rotation to pressure support</li>
        <li>Sample: 2,945 galaxies with integral field spectroscopy</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="section-2">Methods</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Jeans Anisotropic MGE (JAM) dynamical modelling</li>
        <li>Multi-Gaussian Expansion (MGE) for surface brightness</li>
        <li>Orbital anisotropy parameter β = 1 - (σ_t/σ_r)²</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="section-3">Relevance to Galaxy Evolution</h2>
      <p>
        Direct dynamical evidence for galaxy bimodality. The transition at M* ≈ 10^10.5 M☉ aligns with the established quenching mass scale.
      </p>

      <h2 id="section-4">Concepts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/concepts/galaxy-bimodality">Galaxy bimodality</a></li>
        <li><a href="/concepts/orbital-anisotropy">Orbital anisotropy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/concepts/dynamical-modelling">Dynamical modelling</a></li>
        <li><a href="/concepts/quenching">Quenching</a></li>
      </ul>

      <div class="references">
        <h2 id="section-5">Citation</h2>
        <pre><code>@article&#123;bryant2026sami,&#125;
  title=&#123;The SAMI Galaxy Survey: Internal Orbital Structure...&#125;,
  author=&#123;Bryant, J. J. and others&#125;,
  journal=&#123;arXiv:2603.09917&#125;,
  year=&#123;2026&#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
      </div>

      <p><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.09917" target="_blank">View on arXiv →</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
